## PolyAsyncIterable.toObject() method

Return an object made from the entries of `this`<!-- -->. This method is roughly equivalent to calling `Object.fromEntires(iter.toArray())`<!-- -->.

**Signature:**

```typescript

```

**Returns:**

Promise&lt;Record&lt;K, V&gt;&gt;

A promise to an object composed of the entries yielded by this iterable.

## Remarks

This method is only available for iterations of pairs where the first component is a valid object key type.
